candidates.title: Change s-expressions to use Symbol instead of String
candidates.body:
`String` was a bad name. It corresponds more to symbol, since they are not wrapped in quotes.
This PR renames and updates to a newer version of my s-expr library that supports basic pretty printing

Exposes visualizations in CLI and in the web
candidates.body:
This PR adds the ability to export an egglog graph to SVG via the command line and also renders a live graph in the web viewer. 

It uses the serialization support added in #171 and the graph support in the serialization repo added in https://github.com/egraphs-good/egraph-serialize/pull/4 to do the heavy lifting.

It is the same branch as #147, but I have opened a new PR so that the diff is clearer (the old diff seemed to stop being updated once it was closed).

Also if we want to refer to the changes in that old PR for posterity, we can continue looking at it in its frozen state.
